Member Function Documentation

base::String gaia::webkit::MimeTypeMap::getExtensionFromMimeType ( const base::String &  mimeType)

Return the registered extension for the given MIME type.

Note that some MIME types map to multiple extensions. This call will return the most common extension for the given MIME type.

Parameters:
mimeTypeA MIME type (i.e. text/plain)
Returns:
The extension for the given MIME type or null iff there is none.
static base::String gaia::webkit::MimeTypeMap::getFileExtensionFromUrl ( const base::String &  url) [static]

Returns the file extension or an empty string iff there is no extension.

This method is a convenience method for obtaining the extension of a url and has undefined results for other Strings.

Parameters:
url
Returns:
The file extension of the given url.
